t Andrew  preached in Asia Minor and Greece. He is traditionally believed to have been crucified at Patras in Achaia. He was one of the most popular saints of the Middle Ages and was adopted as the patron of Scotland, Russia, and Greece. It has long been among the most popular boys' names in the English-speaking world, especially in Scotland. Its popularity in England was further enhanced by its use as a British royal name for  Prince Andrew  (  b. 1960 ), the Duke of York."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Andrew Ogilvy of Inchmartine was born in 1400, in Kirkton of Auchterhouse, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Alexander Ogilvy of Auchterhouse Earl of Airlie, was 28 and his mother, Mackintosh, was 15. He married Marjorie Glen on 29 February 1440, in Gowrie, Perthshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1461, in Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1400–1461":"1400–1461","1405–Female":"1405–Surnud","1455–1506":"1455–1506","–1533":"–1533","1373–1421":"1373–1421","1386–Female":"1386–Surnud","1414":"1414","1533":"1533","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1421":"1421","24 July 1421":"24. juuli 1421","1386":"1386","1461":"1461","1373":"1373","29 February 1440":"29. veebruar 1440","1506":"1506","1405":"1405","Perth, Perthshire, Scotland":"Perth, Perthshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Gowrie Castle, Perthshire, Scotland":"Gowrie, Perthshire, Scotland","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Auchterhouse, Forfarshire, Scotland":"Auchterhouse, Angus, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Auchterhouse, Angus, Scotland":"Auchterhouse, Angus, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Kirkton of Auchterhouse, Angus, Scotland":"Kirkton of Auchterhouse, Angus, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1400–1461":"1400–1461","1405–Female":"1405–Kuollut","1455–1506":"1455–1506","–1533":"–1533","1373–1421":"1373–1421","1386–Female":"1386–Kuollut","1414":"1414","1533":"1533","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1421":"1421",